 <H1>Find sid’s of sailors who’ve reserved a red and a green boat</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>INTERSECT: Can be used to compute the intersection of any two  union-compatible sets of tuples. 
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Included in the SQL/92 standard, but some systems don’t support it.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Contrast symmetry of the UNION and INTERSECT queries with how much the other versions differ.</H2>
</UL></P>
<P><UL>
SELECT  S.sid
<BR></UL><UL>
FROM  Sailors S, Boats B1, Reserves R1,
</UL><UL>
             Boats B2, Reserves R2
</UL><UL>
WHERE  S.sid=R1.sid AND R1.bid=B1.bid
</UL><UL>
  AND  S.sid=R2.sid AND R2.bid=B2.bid
</UL><UL>
  AND (B1.color=‘red’ AND B2.color=‘green’)</UL></P>
<P><UL>
SELECT  S.sid
<BR></UL><UL>
FROM  Sailors S, Boats B, Reserves R
</UL><UL>
WHERE  S.sid=R.sid AND R.bid=B.bid
</UL><UL>
                AND B.color=‘red’
</UL><UL>
INTERSECT
</UL><UL>
SELECT  S.sid
</UL><UL>
FROM  Sailors S, Boats B, Reserves R
</UL><UL>
WHERE  S.sid=R.sid AND R.bid=B.bid
</UL><UL>
                AND B.color=‘green’</UL></P>
